a6806cae-a986-44b7-87a1-8fbaf5a2b980.1441825a-dc2f-4b16-8255-ebfc7b8ac978.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow handles all the low-level operations and use-cases for CLU within HPOO, running on HPNA.  This lets HPOO handle the entire request per higher-level inputs, including "overload" variables to the command line using variable-names within ${commands}.

Note\: Actual script libraries on $override_JRAS is running here\:  /data01/hosteng/Common_Library.tcl

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Javascript operator converts local HPOO variables into "index1\=value1 index2\=value2..." format
3) Operator runs command\:/usr/bin/execpt against local RAS script on $override_JRAS

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
runas_vendor	- HPOO needs override $tc_device_vendor$ to interpret prompts properly.  This to bypass CLU trying to get vendor information from HPNA rules.
router		- Device target IP or DNS

Results\:
 flowOutput - Raw data back from ssh/telnet to $router commands

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${router}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${router}

a6806cae-a986-44b7-87a1-8fbaf5a2b980.3730b045-e77e-4543-9bd1-6ef7341c65e3.description=
Wanted to write a script that handles all the low-level operations and use-cases for CLU within HPOO.  This lets HPOO handle the entire request per higher-level inputs, including "overload" variables to the command line using variable-names within ${commands}.

Note\: Actual script example on sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab is running here\:  /data01/clu_direct/${scriptName} ${scriptArgs}

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) inputs\:
device_username	- username -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
device_password	- encrypted password -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
runas_vendor	- HPOO needs override $tc_device_vendor$ to interpret prompts properly.  This to bypass CLU trying to get vendor information from HPNA rules.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

Efficiency\:
checkForNull \= 0.016s
runCLU \= 10.241s
 - Connect to "sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab" and initiate Expect \= 7s
 - Init CLU \= 0s
 - Actual Commands against Router\: 3s
Cleanup .1s

Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

a6806cae-a986-44b7-87a1-8fbaf5a2b980.description=

Brocade commands ran\:
  if {[llength [split "LSAN_${host_check}_${lif_check}" {}]] > 63} then FAIL
  zonecreate z_${custHost}_${vServerPort},"${custHost};${vServerPort}" (zone, member)
  cfgadd $activeConfig,z_${custHost}_${vServerPort}
  cfgsave
  cfgenable $activeConfig
  zoneshow z_${custHost}_${vServerPort}
  zone --validate z_${custHost}_${vServerPort}
  fcping ${custHost_WWPN} ${vServerPort_WWPN}


Synopsis\:
  This flow creates the zone to all AliasLif (multiple) to netapphost (multiple), cfgsave, cfgadd, and runs nszonemember output information.

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Connect to HPNA (JRAS or HPNA), run nszonemember, zonecreate, etc, cfgsave, cfgadd...
3) Output success/failure and new alias info.

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
hostalias_list - host
netapplif_list - lifs to connect to host

Results\:
 flowOutput -new alias information, XML format.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}
